8dad			; https://tutorials.eeems.ca/ASMin28Days/lesson/day16.html#cmp 
8dad			 
8dad			; String Length 
8dad			;With a length-prefixed string, finding the length is trivial. For a null-terminated string, the process is decidedly more involved. This is where CPIR comes in. 
8dad			 
8dad			; Get the length of the null-terminated string starting at $8000 hl 
8dad			;    LD     HL, $8000 
8dad			 
8dad			strlenz: 
8dad			 
8dad af			    XOR    A               ; Zero is the value we are looking for. 
8dae 47			    LD     B, A             ; Since we haven't the slightest clue as to the  
8daf 4f			    LD     C, A             ; actual size of the string, put 0 in BC to search 
8db0			                           ; 65, 536 bytes (the entire addressable memory space). 
8db0 ed b1		    CPIR                   ; Begin search for a byte equalling zero. 
8db2			 
8db2			; BC has been decremented so that it holds -length. Now need to synthesize a NEG BC. 
8db2 67			    LD     H, A             ; Zero HL (basically set it to 65, 536) to get the 
8db3 6f			    LD     L, A             ; number of bytes 
8db4 ed 42		    SBC    HL, BC           ; Find the size. CPIR doesn't affect carry. 
8db6 2b			    DEC    HL              ; Compensate for null. 
8db7 c9				ret 
8db8			 
8db8			; Get the length of the A terminated string starting at $8000 hl 
8db8			;    LD     HL, $8000 
8db8			 
8db8			strlent: 
8db8			 
8db8			                  ; A is the value we are looking for. 
8db8 06 00		    LD     B, 0             ; Since we haven't the slightest clue as to the  
8dba 0e 00		    LD     C, 0             ; actual size of the string, put 0 in BC to search 
8dbc			                           ; 65, 536 bytes (the entire addressable memory space). 
8dbc ed b1		    CPIR                   ; Begin search for a byte equalling zero. 
8dbe			 
8dbe			; BC has been decremented so that it holds -length. Now need to synthesize a NEG BC. 
8dbe 26 00		    LD     H, 0             ; Zero HL (basically set it to 65, 536) to get the 
8dc0 2e 00		    LD     L, 0             ; number of bytes 
8dc2 ed 42		    SBC    HL, BC           ; Find the size. CPIR doesn't affect carry. 
8dc4 2b			    DEC    HL              ; Compensate for null. 
8dc5 c9				ret 
